The paper proposes a data-driven approach for computing the operating envelope in industrial operations, which involves using classifiers such as support vector machines. This suggests that the paper could belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) or Machine Learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the interpretability and implementability of the operating envelope, which could fall under the sub-categories of Systems and Control (cs.SY), Software Engineering (cs.SE), or Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE).
